{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} ''[[publicen]]'' (and publish to look like to ''[[banish]]'', ''[[finish]]''), from {{etyl|fro}} ''[[publier]]'', from {{etyl|la}} {{term|publicare||to make public, show or tell to the people, make known, declare, also (and earlier) confiscate for public use}}, from {{term|publicus||pertaining to teh people, public}}; see [[public]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|pŭb'lĭsh}}, {{IPA|/ˈpʌblɪʃ/}}, {{SAMPA|/"pVblIS/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|publish|es}}

# {{intransitive}}: To [[issue]] a [[publication]].
# {{transitive}}: To issue something (usually [[print]]ed work) for [[sale]] and [[distribution]].
# {{transitive}}: To [[announce]] to the [[public]].

